1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
https://slama.dev/comeback/

2
00:00:05,780 --> 00:00:07,260
Eight Small Hydras.

3
00:00:07,260 --> 00:00:09,250
Lucie Vondráčková, eight.

4
00:00:10,540 --> 00:00:11,740
Five Satan's Boletes.

5
00:00:11,740 --> 00:00:14,550
Honza Nedvěd, five.

6
00:00:15,150 --> 00:00:16,440
Thirty Steel Wools.

7
00:00:16,950 --> 00:00:18,250
Eva Farná, thirty.

8
00:00:20,250 --> 00:00:21,150
I don't get it.

9
00:00:22,150 --> 00:00:22,950
Birthmark.

10
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,380
Fifteen Bald Bores.

11
00:00:26,660 --> 00:00:28,200
Danda, fifteen.

12
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:31,180
Tomáš, how can you keep putting up with this from Ozzák?

13
00:00:31,550 --> 00:00:33,350
He keeps the sales records on this thing.

14
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:35,850
His documents are a mess.

15
00:00:35,960 --> 00:00:38,680
He wallpapered the storage room with the invoices from February 2004.

16
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:44,700
September 2005 blew away in the wind and don't even get me started on June 2006, because I have my dignity.

17
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:45,340
Calm down!

18
00:00:46,250 --> 00:00:48,520
We'll manage everything with Helenka.

19
00:00:49,050 --> 00:00:51,650
Yeah, I already told you, I've had her since... '92.

20
00:00:51,850 --> 00:00:52,750
Seven times.

21
00:00:53,650 --> 00:00:55,560
The first Czech accounting program.

22
00:00:55,850 --> 00:00:58,260
We've been pulling together in business since the start.

23
00:00:58,650 --> 00:01:00,350
And she's never betrayed me.

24
00:01:00,950 --> 00:01:02,220
Unlike our accountant.

25
00:01:02,450 --> 00:01:04,220
You're being unfair to her.

26
00:01:04,250 --> 00:01:06,050
The woman can't count.

27
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:12,650
Yeah, and deserting right before the tax office inspection, that's what I call outright betrayal.

28
00:01:12,740 --> 00:01:14,120
Come, come here, come on.

29
00:01:14,820 --> 00:01:15,440
Careful.

30
00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:25,020
Jesus, this takes forever.

31
00:01:27,450 --> 00:01:29,770
Zoran has the Alexis 2008 program.

32
00:01:30,050 --> 00:01:31,250
You should see it, super fast.

33
00:01:32,450 --> 00:01:34,250
It can even handle creative accounting.

34
00:01:34,450 --> 00:01:38,250
You type in whatever loss you want and it takes care of everything.

35
00:01:38,780 --> 00:01:39,520
No, no.

36
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:42,050
Better slow but proper.

37
00:01:44,450 --> 00:01:48,230
Have a coffee, I'll be done in a bit.

38
00:01:48,230 --> 00:01:48,570
Yeah.

39
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:50,470
I'll put on coffee for him.

40
00:01:50,470 --> 00:01:56,750
I'll have some when I feel like it.

41
00:01:57,950 --> 00:02:06,550
Once the inspectors get everything from Helenka nice and tidy in neat columns, they won't even think to look at the state of our paperwork.

42
00:02:07,350 --> 00:02:12,770
And that's the point, because sometimes they look like someone used them to clog a toilet drain.

43
00:02:12,770 --> 00:02:14,130
You mean March 2006?

44
00:02:16,250 --> 00:02:18,850
For God's sake.

45
00:02:19,450 --> 00:02:20,730
He actually did that?

46
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:23,050
Luckily he was just straining mortar through them.

47
00:03:04,940 --> 00:03:06,700
Tomáš, I've found out.

48
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:11,350
Still says error disk?

49
00:03:11,490 --> 00:03:12,090
Yeah.

50
00:03:13,450 --> 00:03:16,550
You know, Tomáš, it could be worse.

51
00:03:17,050 --> 00:03:17,850
It can't.

52
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:20,550
Iva called a moment ago.

53
00:03:21,050 --> 00:03:23,650
She went with Saša to meet the Dalai Lama.

54
00:03:24,050 --> 00:03:26,450
Lexa couldn't go because he has chicken pox.

55
00:03:27,350 --> 00:03:29,050
That's not so terrible.

56
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:32,950
The girls took Ozzák instead.

57
00:03:33,350 --> 00:03:35,950
Do you still think it could be worse?

58
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:37,250
It could.

59
00:03:38,150 --> 00:03:40,950
I've already found out who they're sending from the tax office.

60
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:43,450
It's Otto Schluss.

61
00:03:43,950 --> 00:03:44,850
Otto Schluss?

62
00:03:45,250 --> 00:03:46,450
Bulldog Otto.

63
00:03:46,950 --> 00:03:48,610
A few years ago he audited the electric company.

64
00:03:48,950 --> 00:03:51,350
They had to raise electricity prices to cover the penalties.

65
00:04:01,760 --> 00:04:02,360
Twice.

66
00:04:04,450 --> 00:04:05,750
Ozzák sold some music.

67
00:04:06,450 --> 00:04:09,150
Halloween, two copies.

68
00:04:09,440 --> 00:04:10,260
Hi, dad.

69
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:11,840
Peace be with you.

70
00:04:12,150 --> 00:04:12,900
Where's Ozzák?

71
00:04:13,150 --> 00:04:14,550
Was he arrested or did he escape?

72
00:04:15,550 --> 00:04:16,350
Bro, don't you know I banned you from religious events ever since you told the Pope about goulash with sixers?

73
00:04:21,550 --> 00:04:24,110
He shouldn't wear the same hat as the cook at the Rotunda.

74
00:04:24,310 --> 00:04:28,750
He actually didn't embarrass us today, if you don't count the nagging about schnitzels.

75
00:04:28,750 --> 00:04:31,810
Goose schnitzels are part of every feast.

76
00:04:31,950 --> 00:04:34,430
The lecture was called "The Path to Enlightenment."

77
00:04:34,430 --> 00:04:35,150
That's what it was.

78
00:04:35,330 --> 00:04:36,330
Ground floor.

79
00:04:36,750 --> 00:04:38,730
The ground floor had the same squat as the balcony.

80
00:04:39,050 --> 00:04:40,090
Not even a meatball.

81
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:42,850
But that guy in the bedsheet spoke well.

82
00:04:43,050 --> 00:04:46,150
Mr. Ozzák, that was His Holiness the Dalai Lama.

83
00:04:46,150 --> 00:04:46,980
Nonsense.

84
00:04:47,250 --> 00:04:49,850
I can still tell a man from a woman, can't I?

85
00:04:50,050 --> 00:04:53,650
I liked how he said we should seek the light and follow it.

86
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:58,060
And when I told him that's pretty hard because someone keeps stealing the lightbulbs in the bathroom at the Jezevec pub.

87
00:04:58,220 --> 00:04:58,660
Good Lord.

88
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:01,540
So he patted me on the head and gave me this fat guy.

89
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:03,650
He said it'll show me the way.

90
00:05:04,300 --> 00:05:06,560
Then tell it to show you really fast.

91
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:10,540
Come on, if we don't get this sorted soon, we're in big trouble.

92
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:11,500
Big trouble!

93
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:12,540
The Dalai Lama

94
00:05:13,450 --> 00:05:16,850
says that if a problem has a solution, there's no need to worry.

95
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:19,550
If it doesn't, worrying won't help.

96
00:05:21,150 --> 00:05:30,050
I'd like to see your Dalai Lama, what he'd do if his accounting for November was on soup packet wrappers and the tax office inspection is in two days.

97
00:05:30,050 --> 00:05:30,750
Good evening.

98
00:05:30,950 --> 00:05:33,190
And if germ carriers broke into his apartment?

99
00:05:33,550 --> 00:05:34,310
Hey, bro.

100
00:05:34,650 --> 00:05:36,550
Mom says you have to run to the pharmacy for me.

101
00:05:37,050 --> 00:05:40,150
I hope it won't be cod liver oil again, like when I had a broken rib.

102
00:05:40,150 --> 00:05:40,770
So what?

103
00:05:41,350 --> 00:05:43,310
Until you're healthy, don't come in here.

104
00:05:43,310 --> 00:05:43,710
OUT!

105
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:50,490
The Dalai Lama says anger and hatred are like a fishhook.

106
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:53,190
You need to make sure you haven't gotten caught on it.

107
00:05:53,410 --> 00:05:54,190
My thoughts exactly.

108
00:05:54,850 --> 00:06:01,560
Ozzák, if you don't stop bugging me, you'll go look for the invoices from September 2005.

109
00:06:01,560 --> 00:06:03,380
And you know what that means!

110
00:06:05,350 --> 00:06:07,650
Come on, show me the way to the Jezevec.

111
00:06:16,350 --> 00:06:17,290
Free Tibet.

112
00:06:17,750 --> 00:06:18,850
What do you think?

113
00:06:19,050 --> 00:06:19,650
Iva, that suits you.

114
00:06:21,950 --> 00:06:24,350
Lexa, can you even go out in public with those spots?

115
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:24,870
I can.

116
00:06:24,970 --> 00:06:25,390
Shame.

117
00:06:27,450 --> 00:06:29,150
The potassium permanganate isn't working.

118
00:06:29,850 --> 00:06:30,330
Potassium permanganate.

119
00:06:30,330 --> 00:06:34,150
Mom says we're poor and three medicines have to be enough for everything.

120
00:06:34,190 --> 00:06:36,470
Cod liver oil, potassium permanganate, and a jog around the park.

121
00:06:36,650 --> 00:06:38,430
The jog is the worst, but works the best.

122
00:06:38,850 --> 00:06:41,450
I've drunk a whole bottle of that purple gunk and still nothing.

123
00:06:42,550 --> 00:06:43,480
I don't get it.

124
00:06:43,750 --> 00:06:47,940
So if the Tibetans are being oppressed, why don't they make a deal with some big country to protect them?

125
00:06:48,150 --> 00:06:50,350
China, for example, is pretty close.

126
00:06:50,850 --> 00:06:52,620
Ozzák, it's a bit more complicated than that.

127
00:06:52,950 --> 00:06:57,250
Oh sure, they let themselves be oppressed and then look forward to the reincarnation.

128
00:06:58,850 --> 00:07:01,050
They die, get born again and they're fine.

129
00:07:02,180 --> 00:07:03,860
Yeah, you mean reincarnation.

130
00:07:03,860 --> 00:07:07,350
Well, I'd like to be born as something different.

131
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:10,150
Something nice that people are interested in and love.

132
00:07:10,550 --> 00:07:11,520
Like a pony.

133
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:16,150
Well that's going to be tough, because people get reincarnated as animals as punishment for behaving badly.

134
00:07:16,450 --> 00:07:17,350
Really?

135
00:07:18,450 --> 00:07:20,800
I'd want to be Ozzák again in my next life.

136
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:21,640
It suits me.

137
00:07:22,650 --> 00:07:26,160
But when you reincarnate, you're born in a different time and to different people.

138
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:26,740
Oh really?

139
00:07:28,050 --> 00:07:29,190
What if I was born to you?

140
00:07:29,190 --> 00:07:29,750
What?

141
00:07:29,750 --> 00:07:32,850
No, not now, later, when you find yourself a proper man.

142
00:07:32,870 --> 00:07:33,290
Oh man.

143
00:07:33,950 --> 00:07:34,750
Iva, will you marry me?

144
00:07:37,150 --> 00:07:40,070
Lexa, don't you ever ask me that again.

145
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:41,750
Now go and get treatment.

146
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:43,260
Iva.

147
00:07:45,950 --> 00:07:47,450
Sis, you tripped me.

148
00:07:48,850 --> 00:07:50,050
Not good enough for a pony.

149
00:07:57,450 --> 00:07:58,550
Now we'll see.

150
00:07:59,450 --> 00:08:00,250
Careful.

151
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:05,150
You saved them.

152
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:06,130
Shame.

153
00:08:07,840 --> 00:08:09,700
Marcelka, could you go to the back for a moment?

154
00:08:10,950 --> 00:08:22,550
Count how many Boney M. albums we have back there. Good as new.

155
00:08:23,450 --> 00:08:25,750
And clean as the word of God.

156
00:08:29,350 --> 00:08:31,550
So without Helenka you have to re-enter everything?

157
00:08:32,440 --> 00:08:33,080
Wait.

158
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:35,550
You've been entering data into it?

159
00:08:35,650 --> 00:08:38,450
Well of course, it has the accounting in it.

160
00:08:39,150 --> 00:08:41,350
Man, have you lost your mind?

161
00:08:41,450 --> 00:08:42,870
You don't know.

162
00:08:42,870 --> 00:08:43,090
What?

163
00:08:44,030 --> 00:08:45,870
That program was made by a complete nutcase.

164
00:08:45,870 --> 00:08:53,970
He was going through a divorce, was angry at the whole world, so instead of a calculator he built in a random number generator.

165
00:08:53,970 --> 00:08:54,610
So...

166
00:08:55,850 --> 00:08:58,570
But I never needed a calculator.

167
00:08:58,570 --> 00:09:00,150
Helenka always calculated everything herself.

168
00:09:00,950 --> 00:09:02,050
Calculated, more like guessed, like playing the lottery.

169
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:07,010
The odds of getting it right were about one in a million.

170
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:10,440
Only four copies were sold before they figured it out.

171
00:09:10,520 --> 00:09:16,300
One went to the Kladno police, one to IPB bank, and one to some Mrs. Husáčková.

172
00:09:16,340 --> 00:09:18,500
And she was the only one who didn't go to jail.

173
00:09:19,020 --> 00:09:21,760
Because she was the oldest citizen in the Liberec region.

174
00:09:22,580 --> 00:09:23,140
Helenka?

175
00:09:23,540 --> 00:09:25,140
Yeah, right, Helenka, Helenka.

176
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:26,780
That was actually his wife's name.

177
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:29,620
Alright, so here we go.

178
00:09:29,980 --> 00:09:31,160
Nice to meet you.

179
00:09:31,280 --> 00:09:33,380
And I'll send you the invoice.

180
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:35,520
For the accounting, so you have it in order.

181
00:09:35,640 --> 00:09:36,200
Goodbye.

182
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,350
Shall we have a coffee?

183
00:09:46,470 --> 00:09:47,650
Don't worry, Tomáš.

184
00:09:47,790 --> 00:09:49,070
Tomorrow I'll bring Alexis.

185
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:53,050
Maybe we'll manage somehow before that guy from the tax office arrives.

186
00:09:55,350 --> 00:09:55,950
Schluss, Otto.

187
00:09:57,450 --> 00:09:59,350
I believe you were just talking about me.

188
00:10:08,450 --> 00:10:14,750
You see, Mr. Schluss, we've had a rather unpleasant incident.

189
00:10:15,750 --> 00:10:18,430
You haven't by any chance lost your accounting records?

190
00:10:18,430 --> 00:10:19,630
How did you guess?

191
00:10:19,850 --> 00:10:20,950
A lucky guess.

192
00:10:21,550 --> 00:10:23,290
I'll check the original documents.

193
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:26,600
Unless they burned down, or something?

194
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:31,110
And is that a big complication?

195
00:10:31,550 --> 00:10:32,150
Not really.

196
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:39,250
But it makes me grumpy and when I'm grumpy, I tend to be thorough during inspections.

197
00:10:41,450 --> 00:10:42,230
Are you making coffee?

198
00:10:42,650 --> 00:10:43,950
I'll put the water on right away.

199
00:10:44,150 --> 00:10:47,350
One-to-one Arabica with Robusta, unpasteurized milk, goat.

200
00:10:50,450 --> 00:10:51,550
You don't have any.

201
00:10:53,750 --> 00:10:55,970
Well, never mind.

202
00:10:57,050 --> 00:10:58,250
And where will you seat me?

203
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:02,050
By law I'm entitled to a quiet, clean environment.

204
00:11:02,420 --> 00:11:04,240
In the storage room.

205
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:08,100
Here in the storage room you'll have peace and quiet, and it'll be clean too.

206
00:11:08,100 --> 00:11:09,000
Marcelka will sweep.

207
00:11:09,460 --> 00:11:11,750
Do we have a broom?

208
00:11:11,870 --> 00:11:12,250
I'll buy one.

209
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:21,670
This reminds me of the enriched uranium storage where they put me in Temelín.

210
00:11:21,670 --> 00:11:25,520
I felt quite cramped there.

211
00:11:25,580 --> 00:11:27,940
And when I feel cramped...

212
00:11:28,450 --> 00:11:29,750
You get thorough?

213
00:11:31,150 --> 00:11:31,850
Yes, I get thorough.

214
00:11:35,450 --> 00:11:36,190
Just a moment.

215
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:38,550
I just had an idea.

216
00:11:46,650 --> 00:11:48,750
In case you fancy a little snack.

217
00:11:49,050 --> 00:11:50,350
Why thank you.

218
00:11:52,350 --> 00:11:53,950
How did you know I'm on a diet?

219
00:11:54,250 --> 00:11:56,050
Oh come on now.

220
00:11:58,350 --> 00:12:00,050
They had bigger ones in Temelín.

221
00:12:00,550 --> 00:12:01,970
They grow them there themselves.

222
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:07,650
They have a little greenhouse in the cooling tower.

223
00:12:08,710 --> 00:12:10,090
They took good care of me.

224
00:12:10,090 --> 00:12:11,950
I gained 40 kilos there.

225
00:12:12,650 --> 00:12:14,450
You can't even tell.

226
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:17,650
It didn't do them any good.

227
00:12:18,450 --> 00:12:20,350
Then I arranged an audit in Františkovy Lázně.

228
00:12:21,770 --> 00:12:23,330
They prepared a special program for me there.

229
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:26,650
Diet, yoga, meditation.

230
00:12:27,850 --> 00:12:29,150
And how did that turn out?

231
00:12:30,150 --> 00:12:31,350
I'm thin as a reed.

232
00:12:36,550 --> 00:12:40,650
And how long does an audit take for a small company like mine?

233
00:12:41,950 --> 00:12:43,850
A day, two, a year.

234
00:12:45,650 --> 00:12:47,080
It varies.

235
00:12:47,550 --> 00:12:49,050
Depends on how much you find.

236
00:12:49,850 --> 00:12:53,650
But when nothing is found, it goes quickly, right?

237
00:12:53,950 --> 00:12:55,350
Something always turns up.

238
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:57,460
You just have to look hard enough.

239
00:12:57,460 --> 00:13:15,870
Hi, dad.

240
00:13:16,090 --> 00:13:17,030
I'd like to...

241
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:19,570
Ivuška, this is Mr. Schluss.

242
00:13:20,650 --> 00:13:25,450
He's doing our audit, so it doesn't matter what you want, because you should want it somewhere else.

243
00:13:25,450 --> 00:13:27,310
But this is important.

244
00:13:27,670 --> 00:13:29,280
What is it?

245
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,440
A Tibetan flag.

246
00:13:30,620 --> 00:13:32,580
We have to hang it in protest against China.

247
00:13:32,660 --> 00:13:36,400
We tried at school, but the principal told us that human rights have no place at the grammar school.

248
00:13:37,080 --> 00:13:38,600
Well, it won't work here either.

249
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:42,420
Mr. Schluss needs peace and quiet and he couldn't care less about China.

250
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:42,860
Right?

251
00:13:43,230 --> 00:13:44,250
Not at all.

252
00:13:45,150 --> 00:13:47,450
We could learn from China.

253
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:52,350
There, when you owe more than 100,000 yuan in taxes, they chop off both your hands.

254
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,000
Well, you heard him.

255
00:13:55,300 --> 00:13:56,880
No flag and that's final.

256
00:13:56,880 --> 00:14:03,250
Besides, it would block Mr. Schluss's light and when something blocks Mr. Schluss's light, he gets thorough.

257
00:14:04,150 --> 00:14:07,450
Little girl, give me back that pen.

258
00:14:07,460 --> 00:14:08,020
Ouch.

259
00:14:13,650 --> 00:14:14,850
Oh, Saša!

260
00:14:16,650 --> 00:14:18,750
Sorry, she wants to be a pony.

261
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:31,750
And why is he laughing like that?

262
00:14:32,450 --> 00:14:33,950
Because he doesn't give a damn about anything.

263
00:14:35,250 --> 00:14:37,550
He reminds me of a classmate from elementary school.

264
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:38,850
Mirek Kláda.

265
00:14:39,850 --> 00:14:41,150
He had dropsy.

266
00:14:42,050 --> 00:14:42,880
Did he laugh too?

267
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:43,320
All the time.

268
00:14:43,850 --> 00:14:44,950
Then it could be him.

269
00:14:45,950 --> 00:14:49,460
This one can simply say, in my next life I want to be Kláda.

270
00:14:49,950 --> 00:14:50,750
And he is Kláda.

271
00:14:51,050 --> 00:14:53,550
Now that's what I call a win.

272
00:14:54,150 --> 00:14:56,150
And since when are you interested in this stuff?

273
00:14:56,450 --> 00:14:58,550
Since I got to know those Tibetans.

274
00:14:59,450 --> 00:15:01,750
I think reincarnation seems like a pretty good idea.

275
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:07,250
You die, get born again, wait eleven, twelve years and you can drink again.

276
00:15:10,050 --> 00:15:10,750
Hey.

277
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:12,860
Auntie, could I hang this up here?

278
00:15:13,140 --> 00:15:15,440
No football, I don't want my regulars fighting in here.

279
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,120
It's not a party flag.

280
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:18,300
And what regulars?

281
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:21,050
Ozzák would have to fight with himself here.

282
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,750
That's happened before.

283
00:15:26,350 --> 00:15:30,050
Alright, hang it up there, at least it'll cover up that scribble.

284
00:15:30,350 --> 00:15:32,450
Whoa, who did that?

285
00:15:32,750 --> 00:15:33,350
Saša.

286
00:15:33,750 --> 00:15:35,650
She surprised me, that girl.

287
00:15:36,150 --> 00:15:37,290
Did she run out of chalk?

288
00:15:37,290 --> 00:15:38,190
More like courage.

289
00:15:38,190 --> 00:15:40,750
She threw the chalk down, shrieked something, and ran away.

290
00:15:43,450 --> 00:15:45,650
Hey, Ivona, leave it.

291
00:15:45,950 --> 00:15:49,550
What kind of mom would I be if I didn't keep my children's drawings?

292
00:15:50,940 --> 00:15:51,540
Bye.

293
00:15:54,350 --> 00:15:57,450
Mom, I still think it's not working.

294
00:15:58,150 --> 00:15:59,350
So what are you waiting for?

295
00:16:00,150 --> 00:16:01,040
To the park, go.

296
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:02,450
At least three laps.

297
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:14,550
April 2005.

298
00:16:17,550 --> 00:16:19,650
I'm used to a lot, but...

299
00:16:19,950 --> 00:16:26,410
February accounting on election flyers, March on coffee filters, and April on envelope liners?

300
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:28,230
I've never seen that before.

301
00:16:28,850 --> 00:16:33,070
You see, my brother has his own strong views on keeping accounting records.

302
00:16:33,550 --> 00:16:34,750
Very original.

303
00:16:35,250 --> 00:16:37,570
The only thing he hasn't used yet is toilet paper.

304
00:16:37,850 --> 00:16:40,550
Well then you shouldn't audit June 2006.

305
00:16:43,050 --> 00:16:44,450
That's not past the statute of limitations.

306
00:16:44,850 --> 00:16:47,250
We're missing September 2005.

307
00:16:48,450 --> 00:16:50,350
You see, Mr. Schluss...

308
00:16:50,850 --> 00:16:55,450
That September sort of blew away on us.

309
00:16:56,250 --> 00:16:59,350
April on envelope liners and September blew away.

310
00:17:00,450 --> 00:17:03,050
You have one day to get those records together.

311
00:17:03,650 --> 00:17:07,260
And do you think we could somehow manage without that September?

312
00:17:07,260 --> 00:17:07,860
I doubt it.

313
00:17:09,050 --> 00:17:09,950
That would be expensive.

314
00:17:11,650 --> 00:17:13,550
Got any matches?

315
00:17:16,350 --> 00:17:19,350
You think it's time to cover your tracks?

316
00:17:37,150 --> 00:17:42,050
Death is just a gateway to a new life, but people are afraid to walk through it.

317
00:17:42,990 --> 00:17:43,350
Hm?

318
00:17:44,850 --> 00:17:45,650
That was nicely said.

319
00:17:46,050 --> 00:17:48,040
Then it's not Kláda.

320
00:17:48,040 --> 00:17:49,180
He was just grunting.

321
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,800
I wonder what it's like being dead.

322
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:53,260
Why do you keep going on about death?

323
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:56,040
I did something bad and I think I totally wrecked my karma.

324
00:17:57,680 --> 00:17:58,160
Karma.

325
00:17:59,450 --> 00:18:03,550
I lost some invoices for my brother and now I'm scared I'll be in trouble with him because of it.

326
00:18:04,050 --> 00:18:05,740
Like I might get born somewhere else, you know?

327
00:18:06,050 --> 00:18:07,350
Or as something gross.

328
00:18:08,250 --> 00:18:11,150
Like DJ Bobo.

329
00:18:11,350 --> 00:18:16,650
I thought I'd never say this to you of all people, but stop drinking for today.

330
00:18:19,750 --> 00:18:23,750
Today is fading, tomorrow may never come, so what certainty is there in life?

331
00:18:26,050 --> 00:18:27,350
An installment plan.

332
00:18:27,690 --> 00:18:28,290
Right.

333
00:18:33,550 --> 00:18:35,350
What's that flag doing in the window?

334
00:18:35,850 --> 00:18:38,550
It's a symbol that our shop stands on the side of good.

335
00:18:38,950 --> 00:18:40,370
Take it down immediately.

336
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:40,630
Why?

337
00:18:40,750 --> 00:18:43,150
What if some Chinese person came to shop here?

338
00:18:43,330 --> 00:18:45,830
Dad, the Chinese don't shop, the Chinese copy.

339
00:18:47,150 --> 00:18:52,980
Then get yourself a lapel pin, protest as a private citizen and don't drag our business into economic isolation.

340
00:18:53,350 --> 00:18:54,880
Dad, that auditor is still here.

341
00:18:55,050 --> 00:18:56,250
Yes, but don't disturb him now.

342
00:18:56,450 --> 00:18:57,100
He's relaxing.

343
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:59,550
Has he already had his hands on March 2006?

344
00:19:00,230 --> 00:19:00,750
Why?

345
00:19:02,250 --> 00:19:07,550
Well, it's just that he probably wouldn't be happy to find out those weren't coffee filters.

346
00:19:08,970 --> 00:19:09,490
Fine.

347
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:14,140
Three days the flag can stay, then you buy yourself a pin.

348
00:19:14,140 --> 00:19:15,400
Thanks, dad.

349
00:19:16,860 --> 00:19:17,380
Anti-diarrhea pills.

350
00:19:21,150 --> 00:19:23,750
Children, Tomáš, you know, the rebellious phase.

351
00:19:26,650 --> 00:19:28,550
Fine, but why is this rebellion aimed at me.

352
00:19:30,050 --> 00:19:33,830
Marcelka, Schluss wants September 2005.

353
00:19:33,950 --> 00:19:39,650
Jesus, well, I don't know.

354
00:19:40,350 --> 00:19:44,550
Could I bring some invoices from Zoran?

355
00:19:45,650 --> 00:19:49,070
I think tanks, land mines and quickite won't pass Schluss's inspection.

356
00:19:49,070 --> 00:19:51,090
My husband is a businessman, not a mobster.

357
00:19:51,650 --> 00:19:54,330
But you said he fired a bazooka on New Year's Eve.

358
00:19:55,650 --> 00:19:58,850
Anyway, Schluss said it's going to be expensive without that September.

359
00:20:01,350 --> 00:20:04,450
I'm not going to send my own brother to his death over the tax office.

360
00:20:22,150 --> 00:20:23,150
Mirek Kláda?

361
00:20:29,150 --> 00:20:30,250
So you came from there?

362
00:20:31,150 --> 00:20:31,950
For the audit.

363
00:20:34,350 --> 00:20:35,610
I wouldn't have expected you here.

364
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:36,950
Nobody does.

365
00:20:38,050 --> 00:20:39,050
Still got that sense of humor.

366
00:20:40,250 --> 00:20:46,050
Hey, do you remember anything from before you came here?

367
00:20:47,250 --> 00:20:48,150
What was it like there?

368
00:20:49,530 --> 00:20:50,050
Cramped.

369
00:20:50,850 --> 00:20:52,050
And enlightenment, did you experience it?

370
00:20:52,650 --> 00:20:53,650
Fortunately not.

371
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:56,310
I had a dosimeter.

372
00:20:56,310 --> 00:20:56,870
A dosimeter?

373
00:20:58,150 --> 00:20:59,650
So they have dosimeters there?

374
00:21:00,550 --> 00:21:01,650
They're mandatory there.

375
00:21:02,350 --> 00:21:03,450
I know why you came.

376
00:21:05,350 --> 00:21:06,750
Because of those invoices, right?

377
00:21:06,950 --> 00:21:08,150
That too.

378
00:21:09,850 --> 00:21:12,750
So if I bring that September, we'll be cool?

379
00:21:13,150 --> 00:21:14,850
Definitely more than now.

380
00:21:15,140 --> 00:21:15,700
Thanks.

381
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:17,150
You're a legend.

382
00:21:40,730 --> 00:21:42,010
You know, Mr. Schluss...

383
00:21:42,010 --> 00:21:42,750
Yes?

384
00:21:43,850 --> 00:21:46,950
Spending time together like this...

385
00:21:46,950 --> 00:21:53,210
I've realized how easily friendship between men can develop.

386
00:21:53,210 --> 00:21:53,850
You think so?

387
00:21:57,250 --> 00:22:01,260
Well yes, that's why I'd very much like to give you this little something.

388
00:22:03,250 --> 00:22:05,150
Well, so you'll remember me fondly...

389
00:22:05,670 --> 00:22:06,830
I'm the one who wrote the introduction.

390
00:22:08,450 --> 00:22:10,950
South Bohemia in Photography.

391
00:22:12,850 --> 00:22:17,850
You might like the photograph on page 246.

392
00:22:20,550 --> 00:22:21,350
Boubín.

393
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:24,050
I don't like it.

394
00:22:25,650 --> 00:22:28,810
No, 346, I made a mistake, 346.

395
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:45,250
Look, Mr. Pacovský, when I convert this to a percentage of income, you're offering me more than the guys from the electric company, but let's each stay on our own side of the barricade.

396
00:22:47,350 --> 00:22:50,770
So we can't do without September 2005.

397
00:22:52,050 --> 00:22:54,750
Do you even realize what an inhuman system you're part of?

398
00:22:57,350 --> 00:23:10,270
A system that forces a person to choose between debtors' prison and frying his own brother?

399
00:23:11,250 --> 00:23:14,250
Bro, I've got September 2005.

400
00:23:17,550 --> 00:23:20,750
That fat guy showed me the way.

401
00:23:23,150 --> 00:23:25,890
Well you see, you just have to look hard enough.

402
00:23:28,150 --> 00:23:37,150
So to sum it up, something always turns up.

403
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:43,250
However, compared to Temelín, it wasn't exactly a big explosion.

404
00:23:44,450 --> 00:23:49,950
But I had to reassess your tax for the years 2003, 2005 and 2006.

405
00:23:50,750 --> 00:23:55,250
Such errors in the totals, I've never seen the likes.

406
00:23:55,450 --> 00:24:02,450
Nevertheless, the total comes to 120,378 crowns.

407
00:24:02,750 --> 00:24:04,350
But...

408
00:24:05,450 --> 00:24:14,810
However, for the years 2004 and 2007 you have such absurd overpayments for the same reason that we'll actually be returning 8 crowns to you.

409
00:24:14,950 --> 00:24:18,150
You can request them by registered mail.

410
00:24:19,150 --> 00:24:20,350
Well, take care.

411
00:24:21,150 --> 00:24:25,050
I've got the Czech Gas Company next.

412
00:24:29,310 --> 00:24:29,710
Goodbye.

413
00:24:32,250 --> 00:24:33,950
I haven't heard that in a long time.

414
00:24:41,750 --> 00:24:43,650
Someone should have a talk with Saša.

415
00:24:44,880 --> 00:24:45,280
Yeah.

416
00:24:49,950 --> 00:24:50,350
Helenka.

417
00:24:57,220 --> 00:24:59,100
You came out better than one acquaintance of mine.

418
00:24:59,180 --> 00:25:00,320
I didn't want to tell you.

419
00:25:00,320 --> 00:25:04,550
But when he found out Schluss was coming for an audit, he set fire to his asbestos mine.

420
00:25:08,250 --> 00:25:11,020
He even caught him putting the gasoline in his expenses.

421
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:13,550
Tomáš, I have a gift for you.

422
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:15,040
Please.

423
00:25:15,940 --> 00:25:17,080
Alexis 2008.

424
00:25:21,650 --> 00:25:22,850
Recommended by the Icelandic Ministry of Finance and Viktor Kožený.

425
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:24,940
Good day.

426
00:25:25,820 --> 00:25:26,400
Hi, mom.

427
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:28,340
I see the spots are gone.

428
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:30,700
Nothing like a good run in the park, right?

429
00:25:31,220 --> 00:25:32,420
Actually, I went to the doctor.

430
00:25:32,560 --> 00:25:35,620
The teacher sent me there because she couldn't stand looking at my spotty face anymore.

431
00:25:35,780 --> 00:25:37,640
Well, I'll have to have a word with her.

432
00:25:38,250 --> 00:25:40,950
I decide when my kids are sick, got it?

433
00:25:43,050 --> 00:25:45,080
You're not even going to ask me what the doctor said?

434
00:25:45,080 --> 00:25:45,480
Well?

435
00:25:46,150 --> 00:25:50,450
The first spots were apparently just regular rashes and the rest were an allergy to the potassium permanganate.

436
00:25:51,150 --> 00:25:52,850
There were always problems with you.

437
00:25:53,050 --> 00:25:54,950
Want to hear that at least Sašenka got better?

438
00:26:12,250 --> 00:26:14,550
His Holiness is looking for spiritual music.

439
00:26:39,550 --> 00:26:40,580
Your wish shall be granted.

440
00:26:40,950 --> 00:26:42,550
You shall become a pony of Velhase.

441
00:26:42,960 --> 00:26:43,680
Yeah!

442
00:26:54,650 --> 00:26:59,450
Does the young lady know that a pony of Velhase must carry at least twice its own weight?
